3. CALCULATE Soil Moisture with Antecedent Precipitation Index (API) formula¶

API formulaAPI formula


θt1=(θt0−θres)e−dtτ+(θsat−(θt0−θres))(1−e−Pt1dsoil)+θresθt1=(θt0−θres)e−dtτ+(θsat−(θt0−θres))(1−e−Pt1dsoil)+θres
  • θt1θt1 Soil moisture at time t1t1 [m3/m3m3/m3]
  • θt0θt0 Soil moisture at time t0t0 [m3/m3m3/m3]
  • θresθres - Residual soil moisture [m3/m3m3/m3] = 11.288 (min θθ for 2017)
  • θsatθsat - Saturated soil moisture [m3/m3m3/m3] = 53.33 (max θθ for 2017)
  • dtdt - Time step used for the simulation (difference between t1 and t0) [h] = 3 h
  • ττ - Soil moisture drying-out velocity [h] = 100 h
  • dsoildsoil - Soil depth where the SM measurements are performed [mm] = 50 mm

with   Δθ0=θt0−θresΔθ0=θt0−θres,   Δθ1=θt1−θresΔθ1=θt1−θres

4. Calculate PRECIPITATION AND IRRIGATION with inverse of Prism¶

PROPOSAL: Inverted API formulaPROPOSAL: Inverted API formula


with

  Δθ0=θt0−θresΔθ0=θt0−θres

  Δθ1=θt1−θresΔθ1=θt1−θres

Pt1=−dsoillog(1−Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτθsat−Δθ0)Pt1=−dsoillog(1−Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτθsat−Δθ0)
  • θt1θt1 - Soil moisture at time t1t1 [m3/m3m3/m3]
  • θt0θt0 - Soil moisture at time t0t0 [m3/m3m3/m3]
  • Pt1Pt1 - Precipitation (and Irrigation) at time t1t1 [mm]
  • θresθres - Residual soil moisture [m3/m3m3/m3] = 11.288 (min θθ for 2017)
  • θsatθsat - Saturated soil moisture [m3/m3m3/m3] = 53.33 (max θθ for 2017)
  • dtdt - Time step used for the simulation (difference between t1 and t0) [h] = 3 h
  • ττ - Soil moisture drying-out velocity [h] = 100 h
  • dsoildsoil - Soil depth where the SM measurements are performed [mm] = 50 mm
CONDITIONCONDITION


Pt1Pt1 cannot be negative. Pt1≥0Pt1≥0

if   x=(1−Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτθsat−Δθ0)⟶Pt1=−dsoillog(x)x=(1−Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτθsat−Δθ0)⟶Pt1=−dsoillog(x)

−dsoillog(x)≥0⟶x≤1⟶Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτ≥0⟹Δθ1≥Δθ0e−dtτ−dsoillog(x)≥0⟶x≤1⟶Δθ1−Δθ0e−dtτ≥0⟹Δθ1≥Δθ0e−dtτ

CONCLUSION: (θt1−θres)≥(θt0−θres)e−dtτ(θt1−θres)≥(θt0−θres)e−dtτ

This condition is violated if the soil moisture at t1t1 decreases too fast (faster than what the drying-out velocity establish). It will mean that the balance is not correct and precipitation will be negative to compensate the loss of soil moisture.
